# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 10: zone-center (Gamma-point) phonons of silicon from the
# dynamical matrix.
#
# Where Tutorial 9 reads the phonon frequencies off the thermal fluctuations
# of a finite-temperature MD run, here we take the zero-temperature, harmonic
# route: displace each atom by a tiny amount, record the forces induced on
# every atom, and assemble the force-constant (dynamical) matrix by finite
# difference.  Diagonalizing it gives the phonon frequencies AT the Gamma
# point.  It needs only one short, deterministic calculation -- no sampling.
#
# Silicon has the diamond structure: an fcc lattice with a TWO-atom basis.
# We build the 2-atom PRIMITIVE cell (a triclinic rhombohedron, exactly as in
# Tutorial 9 but with a second basis atom at 1/4,1/4,1/4).  Two atoms give a
# 6x6 dynamical matrix and six branches: three acoustic (zero frequency at
# Gamma) and three optical -- the optical branches are the new feature that
# the two-atom basis makes possible.  The Stillinger-Weber potential is the
# same one used for the elastic constants in Tutorial 6.

units       metal
atom_style  atomic
atom_modify map array              # dynamical_matrix needs an atom map
boundary    p p p

# --- diamond-silicon primitive cell (fcc primitive vectors, 2-atom basis) ---
variable    a0 equal 5.4309                 # SW silicon lattice constant
variable    s  equal ${a0}/sqrt(2.0)
variable    s  equal 5.4309/sqrt(2.0)
variable    lx equal ${s}
variable    lx equal 3.84022621794602
variable    ly equal ${s}*sqrt(3.0)/2.0
variable    ly equal 3.84022621794602*sqrt(3.0)/2.0
variable    lz equal ${s}*sqrt(2.0/3.0)
variable    lz equal 3.84022621794602*sqrt(2.0/3.0)
variable    ty equal ${s}/2.0
variable    ty equal 3.84022621794602/2.0
variable    tz equal ${s}/(2.0*sqrt(3.0))
variable    tz equal 3.84022621794602/(2.0*sqrt(3.0))

lattice     custom ${a0}                                      a1 0.7071068 0.0       0.0                        a2 0.3535534 0.6123724 0.0                        a3 0.3535534 0.2041241 0.5773503                  basis 0.0  0.0  0.0                               basis 0.25 0.25 0.25
lattice     custom 5.4309                                      a1 0.7071068 0.0       0.0                        a2 0.3535534 0.6123724 0.0                        a3 0.3535534 0.2041241 0.5773503                  basis 0.0  0.0  0.0                               basis 0.25 0.25 0.25
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 7.6804526 4.4343108 3.1355317
region      box prism 0 ${lx} 0 ${ly} 0 ${lz} ${ty} ${ty} ${tz} units box
region      box prism 0 3.84022621794602 0 ${ly} 0 ${lz} ${ty} ${ty} ${tz} units box
region      box prism 0 3.84022621794602 0 3.32573346102029 0 ${lz} ${ty} ${ty} ${tz} units box
region      box prism 0 3.84022621794602 0 3.32573346102029 0 3.13553157694194 ${ty} ${ty} ${tz} units box
region      box prism 0 3.84022621794602 0 3.32573346102029 0 3.13553157694194 1.92011310897301 ${ty} ${tz} units box
region      box prism 0 3.84022621794602 0 3.32573346102029 0 3.13553157694194 1.92011310897301 1.92011310897301 ${tz} units box
region      box prism 0 3.84022621794602 0 3.32573346102029 0 3.13553157694194 1.92011310897301 1.92011310897301 1.1085778203401 units box
create_box  1 box
